The `conductor` cluster vendors the conductor-loop skills from:

    robertbarclayy/conducty  —  https://github.com/robertbarclayy/conducty  —  MIT License

The 19 `conducty-*` loop skills (shape, plan, trace/execute, verify, checkpoint,
debug, improve, review, code-review, ship, system, tdd, terse, dialectic,
context, obsidian, vault-graph, bootstrap, worktrees) are vendored as on-demand
spokes; each carries `origin: "robertbarclayy/conducty (MIT)"` in its frontmatter.
This project's added contribution here is the `conductor-orchestrator` and
`conductor-core` skills, which wire conducty's Execute step to the skill-clusters
resolver (`scripts/resolve-task.mjs`) so each task dispatches to the right cluster —
the closed-loop integration across PAI, spec-kit, conducty, and skill-clusters
documented in `docs/CONDUCTOR-INTEGRATION.md`.
